"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT account.account_id)\nFROM client\nJOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id\nJOIN account ON disp.account_id = account.account_id\nJOIN district ON account.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE client.gender = 'F' AND district.A3 = 'south Bohemia';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct accounts held by female clients in the region of South Bohemia. It joins the necessary tables using the foreign key relationships and applies the conditions specified in the evidence."